window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Nothing is as it seems….</p> <p>After the hacker attack that almost killed Kai and his entire team, everyone at Helltek is on edge. Worse, all evidence points to the saboteur being an employee of the company. Kai not only fears for his and his friends’ safety but the suspicion someone close to him might be the one responsible is disturbing. And that’s just one of Kai’s problems.</p> <p>His nightmares have worsened and he almost suffers another heart attack in his sleep. The God in the Machine is after him, and he’s getting closer every day. If that wasn’t bad enough, Raven, Alice’s sociopathic boyfriend, has sworn to kill Kai. This doesn’t stop Kai from meeting Alice in secret, and it is her who reveals to him what the God in the Machine truly is—a truth far more horrifying than Kai ever could have imagined.</p> <p>Kai finds himself in the center of conspiracies and intrigues that redefine everything he thought he knew about VR. Everyone has their own agenda and it’s becoming more difficult to distinguish between friend and foe. Meanwhile, the saboteur and the people they work for are preparing their final blow and the God is lurking in the Dark Net, waiting to strike….</p>"; 
